00/wsj_0044:Use of Scoring High is widespread in South Carolina and common in Greenville County, Mrs. Yeargin's school district. 
00/wsj_0044:Since the reforms went in place, for example, no state has posted a higher rate of improvement on the Scholastic Aptitude Test than South Carolina, although the state still posts the lowest average score of the about 21 states who use the SAT as the primary college entrance examination.
