00/wsj_0044:When test booklets were passed out 48 hours ahead of time, she says she copied questions in the social studies section and gave the answers to students. 
00/wsj_0044:Mrs. Yeargin admits she made a big mistake but insists her motives were correct. "I was trying to help kids in an unfair testing situation," she says. "Only five of the 40 questions were geography questions.
