01/wsj_0192:Farmers are in the best position of many years to push up corn prices.
01/wsj_0192:In parts of Iowa, for example, some grain elevators are offering farmers $2.15 a bushel for corn.
01/wsj_0192:Many farmers probably wouldn't sell until prices rose at least 20 cents a bushel, said Lyle Reed, president of Chicago Central & Pacific Railroad Co. of Waterloo, Iowa. 
