03/wsj_0349:The exchange also may step up its disclosure of firms engaged in program trading, these people said. 
03/wsj_0349:Mr. Phelan said that the Big Board has been trying to deal quietly with the issue, but that banning computer-assisted trading strategies entirely, as some investors want, would be like "taking everybody out of an automobile and making them ride a horse." 
03/wsj_0349:Mr. Phelan hasn't been making public remarks in recent days, and many people have urged him to take more of a leadership role on the program trading issue. 
03/wsj_0349:"The collar was penetrated on a number of occasions," meaning securities firms figured out ways to conduct program trades to circumvent the collar and use the Big Board's electronic trading system, Mr. Phelan said.
03/wsj_0349:Exchange officials emphasized that the Big Board is considering a variety of actions to deal with program trading.
03/wsj_0349:People familiar with the exchange said another idea likely to be approved is expanding the monthly reports on program trading to cover specific days or even hours of heavy program trading and who was doing it. 
03/wsj_0349:In stock-index arbitrage, traders buy and sell large amounts of stock with offsetting trades in stock-index futures to profit from fleeting price discrepancies between the two markets. 
03/wsj_0349:Also, CS First Boston Inc. 's First Boston Corp. unit, the fifth-biggest program trader in September, is "preparing a response" to the program-trading outcry, officials of the firm said.
03/wsj_0349:First Boston is one of the few major Wall Street firms that haven't pulled back from program trading in recent days. 
03/wsj_0349:Mr. Phelan is an adroit diplomat who normally appears to be solidly in control of the Big Board's factions.
03/wsj_0349:If bringing the message is a crime, I'm guilty of it." But he said this doesn't mean he is satisfied with the market's big swings. 
03/wsj_0349:"We're trying to take care of a heck of a lot of constituents," Mr. Phelan said. "Each one has a different agenda." 
03/wsj_0349:For example, in a special meeting Monday with Mr. Phelan, senior officials of some of the Big Board's 49 stock specialist firms complained that the exchange is no longer representing their interests. "We are looking for representation we haven't had," a specialist said. "We've had dictation." 
03/wsj_0349:After another session Mr. Phelan held yesterday with major brokerage firms such as Morgan Stanley & Co., Goldman, Sachs & Co., PaineWebber Group Inc. and First Boston -- all of which have engaged in program trading -- an executive of a top brokerage firm said, "Clearly, the firms want the exchange to take leadership." 
03/wsj_0349:The basket product, while it has got off to a slow start, is being supported by some big brokerage firms -- another member of Mr. Phelan's splintered constituency. 
03/wsj_0349:Mr. Phelan has had difficulty convincing the public that the Big Board is serious about curbing volatility, especially as the exchange clearly relishes its role as the home for $200 billion in stock-index funds, which buy huge baskets of stocks to mimic popular stock-market indexes like the Standard & Poor's 500, and which sometimes employ program trading.
03/wsj_0349:What I'm trying to say to people is, it's proper to worry about program trading, but it's only a piece of the business." 
03/wsj_0349:For example, Mr. Phelan said that big institutions have so much control over public investments that they can cause big swings in the market, regardless of index arbitrage. "A lot of people would like to go back to 1970," before program trading, he said. "I would like to go back to 1970.
03/wsj_0349:Indeed, Mr. Phelan said that if stock-market volatility persists, the U.S. may lose its edge as being the best place to raise capital. "Japan's markets are more stable," he said. "If that continues, a significant number of {U.S.} companies will go over there to raise money." 
03/wsj_0349:Lewis L. Glucksman, vice chairman of Smith Barney, Harris Upham & Co., said: "This is a problem that's taking on a life of its own.
03/wsj_0349:The program trading situation seems to have driven individual investors as well as others out of the market, and even Europeans are suspicious.
