03/wsj_0387:Safety advocates and members of Congress, calling babies "the neglected population," are stepping up a campaign for the mandatory use of infant safety seats on all flights.
03/wsj_0387:But the Federal Aviation Administration is reluctant to require separate seats for babies because of the added cost for traveling parents. 
03/wsj_0387:Some FAA officials note that few infants have been killed in plane crashes, raising the question of whether safety seats really are needed.
