03/wsj_0387:"Infants', toddlers' and young children's safety should no longer be ignored as if they don't count," Mrs. Tsao wrote to the board in advocating use of the safety seats. 
03/wsj_0387:But it is almost impossible to keep hold of a baby during an air crash, or even in severe turbulence. 
03/wsj_0387:During the Sioux City crash, Lori Michaelson of Cincinnati lost her grip on her baby as the plane lurched and tipped over.
03/wsj_0387:The FAA encourages the use of safety seats, but in the past many parents have run into problems trying to use them, even when the plane was only half-full or they had bought an extra ticket especially for the baby. 
03/wsj_0387:When Vanessa Merton, an associate dean at Pace University School of Law, decided to take her young son to Europe last spring, she called four carriers to ask about their policies on car seats. "The people acted like I was transporting heroin," she says.
