04/wsj_0453:They trotted out another crop of instant commercials after the sudden market dip a few weeks ago.
04/wsj_0453:They chance alienating the customers they hope to woo by looking like opportunistic sharks. "People see extra messages in advertising, and if a manufacturer is clearly trying to get something out of it . . . if it's too transparent . . . then consumers will see through that," warns John Philip Jones, chairman of the advertising department at the Newhouse School of Public Communications at Syracuse University. 
