05/wsj_0524:As a model of capitalist efficiency on southern China's doorstep, Hong Kong's prospects look good.
05/wsj_0524:Outflows of people and capital from Hong Kong have been growing since the sovereignty issue first arose in the early 1980s.
05/wsj_0524:Maureen Fraser, an economist with W.I. Carr, a subsidiary of France's Banque Indosuez, believes that the territory may not be able to regain its momentum until some time after 1997.
