07/wsj_0723:European Community employers fear that the EC Commission's plans for a "charter of fundamental social rights" is a danger to industrial competitiveness. 
07/wsj_0723:"We don't want Brussels deciding conditions for workers unless they are necessary and useful," said Zygmunt Tyszkiewicz, secretary general of the employers' confederation Unice. 
07/wsj_0723:Unice -- an acronym for the Union of Industrial and Employers' Confederations of Europe -- fears that the charter will force EC countries to adopt a single pattern in labor relations.
