07/wsj_0742:The S&P 500 index futures "transferred the identity of 500 stocks into one unit-making them a simple commodity to trade," says George Kegler, senior vice president at A. Webster Dougherty in Philadelphia. "It took away the need to know the bad third-quarter report of IBM, for example," Mr. Kegler says. 
