09/wsj_0982:Assets of the 400 taxable funds tracked by IBC/Donoghue's Money Fund Report jumped to $351.2 billion in the week ended Tuesday, the Holliston, Mass.-based newsletter said.
09/wsj_0982:Meanwhile, the average yield on taxable funds dropped nearly a tenth of a percentage point, the largest drop since midsummer.
09/wsj_0982:"Lower yields are just reflecting lower short-term interest rates," said Brenda Malizia Negus, editor of Money Fund Report.
09/wsj_0982:Money funds invest in such things as short-term Treasury securities, commercial paper and certificates of deposit, all of which have been posting lower interest rates since last spring. 
09/wsj_0982:The average yield on six-month CDs of $50,000 or less at major banks was 7.96% in the week ended Tuesday, according to Banxquote Money Markets, a New York information service. 
09/wsj_0982:One way that money fund managers boost yields in a declining rate environment is by extending the maturities of their investments, so they can earn the current higher rates for a longer period.
09/wsj_0982:The average maturity of the taxable funds that Donoghue's follows increased by two days in the latest week to 40 days, its longest since August. 
09/wsj_0982:"They're anticipating further declines in rates and they're going to get them, slowly," said Walter Frank, chief economist for the Donoghue Organization, publisher of Money Fund Report. 
09/wsj_0982:Average maturity was as short as 29 days at the start of this year, when short-term interest rates were moving steadily upward.
09/wsj_0982:The average seven-day compound yield of the funds reached 9.62% in late April. 
09/wsj_0982:The top-performing fund in the latest week was Dreyfus Worldwide Dollar, with a seven-day compound yield of 9.45%.
09/wsj_0982:The average seven-day simple yield of the 400 funds fell to 8.14% from 8.21%, Donoghue's reported.
09/wsj_0983:These people invested in "leveraged" junk bond mutual funds, the publicly traded funds that make a habit of taking out loans to buy extra junk. 
09/wsj_0983:It's a good strategy in a rising market, where a 25% leveraged portfolio in effect allows investors to have 125% of their money working for them.
09/wsj_0983:And shares of leveraged junk funds this year have been clobbered even harder than the junk bonds they hold. 
09/wsj_0983:Leverage is used only by some of the closed-end funds. 
09/wsj_0983:With a leveraged position of about 45%, the fund's share price has plunged 28.5% so far this year.
09/wsj_0983:Leveraged funds in particular "are still extremely vulnerable, because we're still at the beginning of problems in the junk market," says George Foot, a managing partner at Newgate Management Associates in Northampton, Mass. 
09/wsj_0983:Many investors are unaware their funds have borrowed to speculate in such a risky market. "If someone actually sat down and thought about what they were being sold," says Gerald Perritt, editor of the Mutual Fund Letter in Chicago, they might shy away. 
09/wsj_0983:Fund managers, for their part, defend their use of leverage.
09/wsj_0983:Ms. Terry did say the fund's recent performance "illustrates what happens in a leveraged product" when the market doesn't cooperate. "When the market turns around," she says, "it will give a nice picture" of how leverage can help performance. 
09/wsj_0983:He says the fund, which is 40% leveraged, has maintained a "substantial cushion" between its borrowing costs and the yields of the portfolio's bonds. "I don't want to be in a position to have to sell," Mr. Frabotta says. 
