12/wsj_1203:They might even step up sales in a falling market, he said, in an effort to maintain the flow of foreign exchange into their treasuries. 
12/wsj_1203:Technically, Mr. Kaiser noted that a lot of traders had bought into the market when the price was in the $1.24 to $1.26 range, thinking there was support at the $1.20 level.
12/wsj_1203:Betty Raptopoulos, senior metals analyst at Prudential-Bache Securities in New York, agreed that most of the selling was of a technical nature.
