13/wsj_1320:Analysts pointed to reports that the Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries is producing substantially more than its official limit of 20.5 million barrels a day, with some accounts putting the 13-nation group's output as high as 23 million barrels a day. 
13/wsj_1320:That level of production didn't take its toll on futures prices for the fourth quarter, when demand is traditionally strong.
13/wsj_1320:But because first-quarter demand is normally the weakest of the year, several market participants say, OPEC production will have to decline to keep prices from eroding further.
