13/wsj_1368:The goal of most U.S. firms -- joint ventures -- remains elusive.
13/wsj_1368:Because the Soviet ruble isn't convertible into dollars, marks and other Western currencies, companies that hope to set up production facilities here must either export some of the goods to earn hard currency or find Soviet goods they can take in a counter-trade transaction. 
