14/wsj_1416:It is naivete to equate a government's policies with the will of the people (as we well know), and it is even worse folly to merge the clearly divergent agendas of Fidel and the military and the state bureaucracy.
14/wsj_1416:I think it's a little disingenuous to be surprised that Fidel doesn't invite the U.S. State Department to violate the jurisdiction of the Cuban government over its own territory. 
14/wsj_1416:We badly need to follow fact rather than the rhetoric of conventional wisdom.
14/wsj_1416:Without this basic level of attention to reality, our policies on Cuba will continue to be as counterproductive as they have for 30 years.
14/wsj_1416:From my own point of view, given the qualities of humanity, creativity and warm spirit in which the Cuban people excel, we deny ourselves access to things we hold dear, and which seem to run in such short supply these days.
