14/wsj_1443:Immunex Corp. said its scientists isolated a molecule which may hold potential as a treatment for disruptions of the immune-system, ranging from organ-transplant rejection, to allergies and asthma. 
14/wsj_1443:The molecule is the mouse version of a protein called the interleukin-4 receptor.
14/wsj_1443:IL-4 is a hormone which directs the growth and function of white blood cells involved in the body's immune response.
14/wsj_1443:The IL-4 receptor on the surface of such cells receives the hormone's message to rally the body's defense. 
14/wsj_1443:A soluble form of the receptor might turn off a specific part of the immune response without general immune suppression, the company said. 
14/wsj_1443:The IL-4 receptor is one of five such receptors to be developed and tested by Receptech Corp., a spinoff of Immunex, through a proposed $30 million initial public offering.
14/wsj_1443:Immunex will contract with the spinoff to provide the research, development and initial testing of the new agents.
