15/wsj_1554:After the close of trading Friday, the Agriculture Department reported that feedlots in the 13 biggest ranch states held 8.06 million cattle on Oct. 1, down 6% from that date a year earlier. 
15/wsj_1554:Feedlots fatten young cattle for slaughter, so a decline signals a tightening supply of beef. 
