16/wsj_1619:As evidence, he cites yesterday's arrangement for the final financing of a $3 billion bid for American Medical International Inc. in which Chemical served as both the lead bank and an equity investor. 
16/wsj_1619:A Paramount spokesman says that decision was based on the financial, not political, drawbacks of junk bonds. 
16/wsj_1619:But some observers believe Paramount Chairman Martin Davis wanted to avoid the possible taint of being perceived as a corporate raider in his controversial bid for Time.
16/wsj_1619:The success of the NWA financing, and the failure of the UAL deal, also seem to highlight the important new role in takeover financing being played by Japanese banks. 
