16/wsj_1631:Such titles are designed to convey a sense of dignified, broad-scale competence and expertise in selling today's myriad financial products.
16/wsj_1631:The names of some of these products don't suggest the risk involved in buying them, either. 
16/wsj_1631:Indeed, conservative investors, many of them elderly, have poured more than $50 billion into such funds, which promise fatter yields than ordinary Treasury bonds -- only to learn later that these funds use part of their money to dabble in high-risk bond options, a gambler's game. 
