18/wsj_1819:But lawyers said Mr. Steinberg probably faced much more potential liability because, when he sued Disney during his takeover battle, he filed on behalf of all shareholders.
18/wsj_1819:When Mr. Trump sued Bally, he sued only on behalf of himself. 
18/wsj_1819:Mr. Trump and Bally also appeared to have some leverage in the case because in the state of Delaware, where Bally is incorporated, courts have held that greenmail is often protected by the business-judgment rule.
18/wsj_1819:That rule gives boards of directors wide latitude in deciding how to deal with dissident shareholders. 
