19/wsj_1903:Mr. Lang feels that Time's priorities changed. "Their management changed right after {the venture was formed}, and I don't think they were comfortable getting into the competitive wars of women's service magazines." 
19/wsj_1903:Today, Mr. Lang believes his magazines will offer what many women's magazines don't. "We write straight for women on their level," he said. "We don't have passive readers." Mr. Lang points out that even Success, in part, fits the company's image, since about 30% of its readership is female. 
