23/wsj_2379:Jeremiah Mullins, the OTC trading chief at Dean Witter Reynolds in New York, said proudly that his company executed every order it received by the close of trading.
23/wsj_2379:Market makers keep supplies of stock on hand to maintain orderly trading when imbalances occur.
23/wsj_2379:Two years ago, faced with the possibility of heavy losses on the stocks in their inventories, market makers themselves began dumping shares, exacerbating the slide in OTC stock prices. 
23/wsj_2379:Mr. Tarantino of Hambrecht & Quist said some prices fell without trades taking place, as market makers kept dropping the prices at which they would buy shares. "Everyone was hitting everyone else's bid," he said. 
23/wsj_2379:I don't know of anyone carrying big inventories now," said Mr. King of Robinson-Humphrey. 
