24/wsj_2444:Of all the one-time expenses incurred by a corporation or professional firm, few are larger or longer term than the purchase of real estate or the signing of a commercial lease. 
24/wsj_2444:To take full advantage of the financial opportunities in this commitment, however, the corporation or professional firm must do more than negotiate the best purchase price or lease terms.
24/wsj_2444:Specifically, it must understand how real-estate markets overreact to shifts in regional economies and then take advantage of these opportunities. 
24/wsj_2444:Because real-estate purchases and leases are such major long-term commitments that most companies and individuals make these decisions only when confident of future economic stability and growth. 
24/wsj_2444:For example, residential building permits in the trough year of 1982 were off 76% from the 1979 peak level. 
24/wsj_2444:Building permits, for example, soared a staggering 400% between 1982 and the peak year of 1986. 
24/wsj_2444:Look no further than metropolitan Houston and Denver, two of the most depressed, overbuilt and potentially undervalued real-estate markets in the nation.
24/wsj_2444:Of course, some observers have touted Houston and Denver for the past five years as a counter-cyclical play.
24/wsj_2444:The vacancy rate soared more than 20% in nearly every product category, and more than 30% of office space was vacant.
24/wsj_2444:To some observers, the empty office buildings of Houston's "see-through skyline" were indicative of a very troubled economy. 
24/wsj_2444:Its population has continued to increase since 1983, the peak year of the economic cycle.
24/wsj_2444:The rates of increase, however, are less than the rapid growth of the boom years, and this has resulted in a loss of confidence in the economy.
24/wsj_2444:When Denver's regional economy begins to grow faster -- such a recovery could occur as early as next year -- business and consumer confidence will return, and the resulting explosion of real-estate activity will dwarf the general economic rebound. 
24/wsj_2444:Vacancy rates in the 15% to 19% range today may easily rise to the low to mid-20% range in a couple of years.
