24/wsj_2479:Though Holmes Morton fulfills the "requirements" for being a true physician, our so-called sophisticated society and its medical system fail to appreciate the value of such a dedicated physician.
24/wsj_2479:Otherwise, why is there not a rush of funds from medical circles or the related medical-support industry -- i.e. pharmaceutical companies, etc. -- or, most significantly, from all of us to support this doctor and his patients, to support a clinic to further the work of resolving human suffering? 
