24/wsj_2479:The average person can hardly imagine the suspicion, bred by centuries of isolation and persecution, among the Amish toward outsiders and things modern.
24/wsj_2479:This, in my experience, is particularly true of their attitude toward modern medicine.
24/wsj_2479:Dr. Morton's success is not only a measure of the outstanding quality of his work, but also of the desperation the Amish must feel in the face of this horrendous disease. 
24/wsj_2479:Sadly, the article also contains a profound statement about the current state of academe, the professions in particular and American society in general.
